  "description": "Onion Chutney or Vengaya Chutney is a South Indian side dish made with onions, spices and herbs. It is quick, delicious and hot — with a perfect balance of sweet, sour and spicy flavours. Sautéed onions are blended with roasted lentils, peanuts, tamarind and chillies, then finished with a simple tempering. A great alternative when you run out of tomatoes or coconut.",
